Just judging by the amount of people signing up this semester already, if you haven't had your Phase 2 yet it might be difficult. This is probably due to the class just opening for enrollment during Phase 2, so naturally more people are paying attention to it. Definitely try to Phase 2 it if you need it, though.

children.subject: The 10% rule is generally reliable. However, since it does vary, don't think "oh I'm within the 10% I'll probably get in." I'd say because of the fact that this class was just opened and that people are using their Phase 2 units to sign up for this (as opposed to Phase 1 where it is pretty common to add classes that one will drop later), the 10% rule may end up being closer to ~5%. But that's just my speculation based on how 188 was rolled out for enrollment.
Does the 10% rule generally work out for 188? I know it varies depending on the semester, but the 10% rule should still be somewhat dependable still right?

history.content: As a 3rd year Cog-sci Major intending on pursuing a CS minor, is it at all likely to get into 188, or will I probably have to wait till senior year, or is even that not a guarantee? In essence, is it possible to get into 188 without being a CS major?
